        <class name="PointerInfo" line="28">
            <javadoc line="28">
                A class that describes the pointer position.
                  It provides the &lt;code&gt;GraphicsDevice&lt;/code&gt; where the
                  pointer is and the &lt;code&gt;Point&lt;/code&gt; that represents
                  the coordinates of the pointer.
                  &lt;p&gt;
                  Instances of this class should be obtained via{@link MouseInfo#getPointerInfo}.
                  The &lt;code&gt;PointerInfo&lt;/code&gt; instance is not updated dynamically
                  as the mouse moves. To get the updated location, you must call{@link MouseInfo#getPointerInfo} again.                
                <see>
                    MouseInfo#getPointerInfo                    
                </see>
                <author>
                    Roman Poborchiy                    
                </author>
                <since>
                    1.5                    
                </since>
            </javadoc>
